13/08/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Thursday (August 13th) marks the eighth anniversary of the Ohrid Framework Agreement signing, which ended several months of armed conflict in Macedonia. 
The agreement granted more rights to ethnic Albanians and established guidelines for inter-ethnic co-existence. 
On the eve of the anniversary, Deputy Prime Minister for European Integration Vasko Naumovski and Deputy Prime Minister for Implementation of the Framework Agreement Abdulakim Ademi presented certificates to 290 ethnic Albanians. 
They will start work in public administration, in line with provisions for equitable representation of ethnic minorities in state institutions. 
(MIA, MRT, Makfax, A1 - 12/08/09)
